items.name: Princess Elise (Sonic series) LoRA
items.description:
"Sorry for the weird fusions, here Princess Elise as an apology".

Is that what I might say? Nah... I don't regret the fusions, they are interesting experiences and there are people who are attracted by them, just isn't for everyone.

But Princess Elise alone is controversial as well. A human who kissed a dead animal for being in love with him. Don't get me wrong, I also consider the scene as one of the weirdest and most unnecessary scenes in the video game history. But she was chosen, and here she is.

Honestly, she is probably my best model so far. She works very well in checkpoints that focus on 3D realistic fantasy (those usually used for Final Fantasy characters) like Perfect World, and even in Weight 1 generates good results.

You can generate her default design with these prompts:

princesselise, red hair, short hair, blue eyes, white dress, white gloves, high heels, earring, feather ornament, necklace

That makes up for the "one star" I got on the Satori model, right? RIGHT? Just kidding.

Enjoy!

items.name: Multi Controlled Parameters Gif - Auto1111 script
items.description:
This is a personal side project I started mainly to improve my testing methods for Lora collisions for filter out overfitting epochs more reliably.

The concept is simple:

you have the ability to make multiple layers, each one controls a Lora or an attribute that moves from start to end each frame by a value of step size.

There are two types of layers: Prompt layers (like Lora layers) where you can have multiple ones at the same time, and Attribute layers (like a clip skip) where you can have only one for each parameter type.

Tips:

  • Install by moving it to the /Scripts folder.

  • The resulting GIF is not shown after generation; instead, you can find it in Outputs/txt2img-images/txt2gif.

  • When adding a Lora layer, just input its name (e.g., "lora:Steampunk:1"), which becomes "Steampunk."

This script is still in the making, so stuff will most definitely break or have bugs.

items.name: Uzumaki Himawari (Boruto: Naruto Next Generations) LoRA
items.description:
Trained on 41 images. You'll get decent results with any aspect ratio, though I mostly only used 512x512, 512x768, and 768x512.

Strengths

Produces consistently faithful recreations of the character when using the recommended settings below. This lora is also fairly flexible, allowing you to choose which aspects of the character you want to include or exclude in your image, as well as comfortably handling a wide variety of poses and situations.

Shortcomings

Struggles with hands and eyes in some situations, and doesn't seem to play nice with some of the more common checkpoints. Currently it also has trouble with Byakugan eyes, the shinobi outfit, and the white frills on the skirt, but I plan to make improvements to these areas in future versions.

For best results I recommend:

  • Use uzumaki_himawari in the beginning of the positive prompt.

  • To prompt accurate character details use: (lines on face), short black hair, blunt bangs, blue eyes, ((yellow hoodie, pink skirt)), black thigh highs, red boots,

  • Using schneed's Ametrine Blend Checkpoint

  • Using this LoRA with CyberAlchemist's Animix - Anime Screenshot-like Style Mix LoRA

  • Use a lora weight around 0.5-0.7. Going over that seems to produce bad results.

  • Use Highres. fix with these settings

    • R-ESRGAN 4X+ Anime6B

    • Hires steps 0

    • Denoising strength 0.7

    • Upscale 1.5

  • Following DitamAI's No more color contamination guide to make sure the colors of the clothing stay consistent. I only isolated yellow, pink, and black (for the hoodie, pleated skirt, and thigh highs).

  • Use Clip skip 2

I plan to continue improving this LoRA with future versions.

If you have suggestions let me know.

items.name: Ancient Ogre (Tekken) LoRA
items.description:
My second attempt at making a model for a 3D character and my first male character.

I believe that on people's priority list about making LoRA for Tekken characters, Ogre is at the bottom of the list so I decided to speed up the process.

Unlike Princess Elise, I'm not very satisfied with this model, despite having learned the character's clothes and hair well, the face always sounds it's from someone else. But that's probably because, again, my resources are limited here. Ogre only had three appearances in Tekken and only in Tekken Tag Tournement 2 does he have a good quality render and 3D model. On the other hand, his face has always been pretty generic, he's just a monster in a humanoid form after all.

So... Yeah. While Elise I had several CG cutscenes frames from Sonic 06, Ogre I was limited to just a few artworks and screenshots, so don't expect the same quality. As always, Weight below 1 is the best result.

Use these prompts for the full look:

aogre, green skin, brown hair, long hair, red eyes, ponytail, aztec crown, aztec shield, aztec bracelet, aztec trunks, aztec anklets, shirtless, barefoot

Not my best model but not my worst either. So it's a 0-0 draw.
